<bibRefCitation author="Campbell and Davies" firstAuthor="Campbell" pageId="16" pageNumber="131" pagination="86 - 124" refId="ref15970" refString="Campbell JM, Davies A (1991) Family Staphylinidae: rove beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Agriculture Canada Research Branch, Publication 1861 / E: 86 - 124." type="book chapter" year="1991">Campbell and Davies (1991)</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of the record above (shown in 
<figureCitation box="[758,846,1645,1671]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[141,174,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[140,1109,873,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[140,1108,873,1601]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 14. The distribution of Bledius basalis, Bledius mandibularis, Bledius neglectus, Bledius opaculus, and Bledius politus in Atlantic Canada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3767193" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3767193/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="131">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). It is associated with coastal areas, as well as inland swamps and lakes, and is found in slightly moist, heavily vegetated sand (
<bibRefCitation author="Herman" box="[360,530,201,228]" firstAuthor="Herman" pageId="17" pageNumber="132" pagination="1 - 171" refId="ref16574" refString="Herman LH, Jr (1976) Revision of Bledius and related genera, Part II. The armatus, basalis, and melanocephalus groups (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 157: 1 - 171." type="journal article" year="1976">Herman 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
